                        GEORGE LOCKYEE
                  . I am an officer of the House of Correction. I pro
duce a certificate of Chiverall's conviction—(Read: "Clerkenwell, April, 1856; 



                        William Jones, Convicted of stealing a coat; 
Confined four months ")—he is the person.





                        GEORGE HODGES
                  . (policeman, S 36). I produce a certificate—(Read: "Central Criminal Court; 


                        James Godwin, Convicted April, 1851, of larceny, after a previous conviction; 
Transported for Seven Years")—I was present at that trial—the prisoner is the person—he has been in the Crimea since then—I know nothing against him since he has returned.

